  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">2018/21 CIVTC Caritas Chad</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The programme amounting to DKK 7.5 million over four years, will be initiated by Caritas Denmark and its local partner to expand the present humanitarian operation to cover development interventions for the rural poor population in marginalised areas of eastern Chad where until now mainly humanitarian responses towards refugees, and to a limited extend host communities, have been implemented. The local partner have experience with implementation of development projects through support from other donors. Using the knowledge from both these experiences and from the humanitarian interventions, Caritas Denmark now wishes to address the regional food insecurity crisis within the livelihood and water sectors. The climate changes within the Sahelian belt is projected by the World Bank to have profound impact on economic growth and social well-being. However, the Government of Chad and local communities are assessed to need capacity support to be able to consider climate change mitigation meassures. Climate change could potentially pose a threat to livelihood prospects as well as migration flows and potentially conflicts. Besides building resilience of selected rural poor, the partner capacity will be strengthened to implement consistently a human rights based approach as the foundation for change with a long-term perspective, as well as increased collaboration and capacity building of local authorities. This capacity building will make communities and local government structures better able to develop and implement inclusive local development plans in future.</narrative>
  </description>
